Gyang Bere, Jos The presidential candidate of the Peopleâ€™s Democratic party (PDP), Alh Atiku Abubakar is leading in three out of four local government areas of Plateau State as collation of results begins. Plateau State INEC returning officer, Prof. Richard Anande, Vice Chancellor University of Agriculture, Makurdi, was still expecting results from other councils. The results collated from Kanke, Mikang and Panshin areas all turned out in favour of Atiku while result from Jos East LGA favoured the presidential candidate of All Progressives Congress (APC), Muhammadu Buhari. The result is as under: Kanke LGA PDP-22,875 APC-17,946 Jos East LGA PDP-8,853 APC-11,847 Mikang LGA PDP-11,262 APC-10,869 Pankshin PDP-30,319 APC-21,607